Because of the aging population, the incidence and prevalence of dementia has 
increased. The most common form of dementia is Alzheimer's disease. The present 
review focuses on the progression and prognosis of this disease, although many 
of the issues discussed can be extrapolated to other types of dementia. Despite 
public education efforts in recent years, dementia continues to have a 
tremendous impact on the patient, the primary caregiver and/or family and 
